Visits Bauchi to interface with national delegates from Bauchi, Yobe States As political activities towards the presidential primary election thicken in the country, one of the leading People Democratic Party Presidential aspirants, Mohammed Hayatuddeen, has declared that he is the most qualified Aspirant for the ticket among those who have picked nomination forms. Mohammed Hayatuddeen who was in Bauchi to meet with PDP stakeholders and national delegates from Bauchi and Yobe states expressed confidence that he possessed all the necessary requirements to win the forthcoming party presidential primaries and eventually the 2023 presidential election. -Advertisement- The presidential hopeful was speaking during the meeting held at the Command, Guest House in Bauchi, ahead of the party’s primary election stressing that he has all it takes to defeat all other contenders in a free and fair atmosphere. He assured that if given the party ticket and goes on to be elected as the next Nigeria’s President, he will work towards immediately addressing challenges in the security, economy, and other sectors of the national economy in order to have a stabilized polity. He further said that Nigeria under his leadership will be on the path of economic growth and development as well as the restoration of its honor and dignity for international recognition and investment. “I am here in Bauchi for a national campaign tour to seek the support of delegates of Bauchi, Yobe, and Gombe states and the essence is that as PDP Presidential aspirant, there is a need for me to have an interaction with you and to tell you that I have the credentials to be able to run for president and win”. “Nigerians should expect me to resolve very quickly, the huge national security problems that are confronting the country, revive the dis-functional economy, and do the needful to reduce the unemployment rate, eradicate poverty,” he said POLL Mohammed Hayatuddeen described his engagement with the PDP delegates in all the states so far visited as fruitful, promising to make a huge difference for the advancement of the country if given the opportunity. He urged the national delegates to ensure that they voted for the right and most qualified amongst all of them stressing that the PDP cannot afford to make the wrong choice which will lead to its defeat again the third time. He also urged the delegates to study his visions and programs very deeply, compare them with what others have, and then conclude who to vote for during the primary elections.